sentences: Gérard Lesne (French pronunciation: ​[ʒeʁaʁ lɛn]; born 15 July 1956) is a French countertenor.

He was originally a rock singer, but in 1979 the tenor Zeger Vandersteene introduced him to René Clemencic, a pioneer of work in the medieval repertoire, and at age 23, Lesne began touring with the Clemencic Consort.

He was originally a rock singer, but in 1979 the tenor Zeger Vandersteene introduced him to René Clemencic, a pioneer of work in the medieval repertoire, and at age 23, Lesne began touring with the Clemencic Consort.
Since 1993, Gérard Lesne has taught annual courses in vocal interpretation at Royaumont Abbey in France.
In 2004, Gerard Lesne was made Chevalier des Arts et des Lettres by the French government, and received the Académie Charles Cros in honorem prize for his career.
